>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2016-07-28T08:38:34.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"jaredthecoder/awesome-vehicle-security","categoryHTML":"<h2>Websites</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.carhackingvillage.com/\">DEFCON Car Hacking Village</a> - Car Hacking exercises from DEFCON 24.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-07-28T05:28:22.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"jaredthecoder/awesome-vehicle-security","categoryHTML":"<h1>Hardware</h1>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://linklayer.github.io/cantact/\">CANtact</a> - \"The Open Source Car Tool\" designed to help you hack your car. You can buy one or make your own following the guide here.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-07-28T05:28:22.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"jaredthecoder/awesome-vehicle-security","categoryHTML":"<h1>Hardware</h1>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://freematics.com/pages/products/arduino-telematics-kit-3/\">Freematics OBD-II Telematics Kit</a> - Arduino-based OBD-II Bluetooth adapter kit has both an OBD-II device and a data logger, and it comes with GPS, an accelerometer and gyro, and temperature sensors.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-07-28T05:28:22.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"jaredthecoder/awesome-vehicle-security","categoryHTML":"<h1>Hardware</h1>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://goodfet.sourceforge.net/hardware/goodthopter12/\">GoodThopter12</a> - Crafted by a well-known hardware hacker, this board is a general board that can be used for exploration of automotive networks.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-07-28T05:28:22.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"jaredthecoder/awesome-vehicle-security","categoryHTML":"<h1>Hardware</h1>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.8devices.com/products/usb2can/\">USB2CAN</a> - Cheap USB to CAN connector that will register a device on linux that you can use to get data from a CAN network.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-07-28T05:28:22.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"jaredthecoder/awesome-vehicle-security","categoryHTML":"<h1>Hardware</h1>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://store.intrepidcs.com/\">Intrepid Tools</a> - Expensive, but extremely versatile tools specifically designed for reversing CAN and other vehicle communication protocols.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-07-28T05:28:22.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"jaredthecoder/awesome-vehicle-security","categoryHTML":"<h1>Hardware</h1>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://redpitaya.com/\">Red Pitaya</a> - Replaces expensive measurement tools such as oscilloscopes, signal generators, and spectrum analyzers. Red Pitaya has LabView and Matlab interfaces, and you can write your own tools and applications for it. It even supports extensions for things like Arduino shields.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-07-28T05:28:22.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"jaredthecoder/awesome-vehicle-security","categoryHTML":"<h1>Hardware</h1>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://greatscottgadgets.com/hackrf/\">HackerSDR</a> - A Software Defined Radio peripheral capable of transmission or reception of radio signals from 1 MHz to 6 GHz. Designed to enable test and development of modern and next generation radio technologies.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-07-28T05:28:22.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"jaredthecoder/awesome-vehicle-security","categoryHTML":"<h2>Applications</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.vanheusden.com/O2OO/\">O2OO</a> - Works with the ELM327 to record data to a SQLite database for graphing purposes. It also supports reading GPS data. You can connect this to your car and have it map out using Google Maps KML data where you drive.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-07-28T05:28:22.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"jaredthecoder/awesome-vehicle-security","categoryHTML":"<h2>Applications</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://kayak.2codeornot2code.org/\">Kayak</a> - Java application for CAN bus diagnosis and monitoring.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-07-28T04:15:16.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"jaredthecoder/awesome-vehicle-security","categoryHTML":"<h2>Applications</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/zombieCraig/UDSim/\">UDSim</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/zombieCraig/UDSim/\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">172</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":172,\"repo\":\"zombieCraig/UDSim\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - GUI tool that can monitor a CAN bus and automatically learn the devices attached to it by watching communications.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-07-28T04:15:16.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"jaredthecoder/awesome-vehicle-security","categoryHTML":"<h2>Applications</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.romraider.com/\">RomRaider</a> - An open source tuning suite for the Subaru engine control unit that lets you view and log data and tune the ECU.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-07-28T04:15:16.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"jaredthecoder/awesome-vehicle-security","categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries and Tools</h2><h3>Python</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/zombieCraig/c0f/\">c0f</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/zombieCraig/c0f/\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">65</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":65,\"repo\":\"zombieCraig/c0f\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A fingerprinting tool for CAN communications that can be used to find a specific signal on a CAN network when testing interactions with a vehicle.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-07-28T04:15:16.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"alebcay/awesome-shell","categoryHTML":"<h2>Command-Line Productivity</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/sebglazebrook/aliases\">aliases</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/sebglazebrook/aliases\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">395</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":395,\"repo\":\"sebglazebrook/aliases\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Contextual, dynamic, organized aliases for bash</li>","updatedAt":"2016-07-28T02:19:43.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"jaredthecoder/awesome-vehicle-security","categoryHTML":"<h2>Podcasts and Episodes</h2><h3>Podcasts</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.trustedsec.com/podcast/\">TrustedSec Podcast</a> - From the people at TrustedSec, leaders in Social Engineering, their episodes often go into recent vehicle vulnerabilities and exploits.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-07-28T02:13:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"jaredthecoder/awesome-vehicle-security","categoryHTML":"<h1>Other Awesome Lists</h1>","itemHTML":"<li>Security\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/paragonie/awesome-appsec\">Application Security</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/paragonie/awesome-appsec\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;mar